properties.text: Originally an exhibition space open to the public throughout 2000, the Millenium Dome became a white elephant in the capital. It's now in use as a music venue.

Britain stepped in the 'noughties' in a jubilant mood, but found itself grappling with a financial crisis, a war in Iraq and a major terror attack on the capital. Britons became more 'social' and everyone had the chance of fame, as reality TV hit our screens.
Reality TV From Pop Idol to Big Brother, X Factor to The Only Way Is Essex, Britons have enjoyed a love affair with reality television.
The Apple iPod revolutionised the music industry and Britain's relationship with technology. The must-have music player spoke to the UK's consumer culture and gave way to the iPhone.
